txt.en: A Torch-bearer has reached the hall, and the fire spreads....
'Do you not yet know better than to attempt to defy Saruman?'
'He does not look kindly on those who defy him!'
'Your puny city will burn tonight, dogs of Dunland!'
'You will rue the day you forsook the White Hand!'
'Servants of the White Hand, bring your flames and your swords!'
'You shall not withstand me, puny weakling....'
'You will pay, weakling! You cannot defeat me....'
'I must get my people out of that building! I fear it will burn to the ground....'
'So you think you are strong, do you?'
'You will not live long enough to enjoy that thought, fool!'
'They have spread the flames! We cannot withstand another torch....'
